<body>
    <h1>Getting Started with Claude =E2=80=94 Setup Guide</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 local-id=3D"ed43f53eca36" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=
=94SetupGuide-GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupGuide">Getting Started =
with Claude =E2=80=94 Setup Guide</h1>
<p local-id=3D"591031232db7">A click-by-click, fool-proof guide for the CX =
&amp; Delivery leadership team. Mirrors the workshop. Work through it top t=
o bottom =E2=80=94 each step assumes the previous one is done.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5e0026fd63ae">Owner: Charlie Delamare<br>
Audience: CX &amp; Delivery Leadership<br>
Estimated time: 30=E2=80=9345 minutes</p>
<hr local-id=3D"edc031c07849">
<h2 local-id=3D"99d888a099f3" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Quickchecklist">Quick checklist</h2>
<p local-id=3D"47ba92869de1">By the end of this guide, you should have all =
of these ticked:</p>
<ul class=3D"inline-task-list" data-inline-tasks-content-id=3D"1923842874">
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"1"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Desk=
top app installed and signed in</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"2"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Slac=
k plugin connected</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"3"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Atla=
ssian plugin connected</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"4"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Micr=
osoft 365 plugin connected</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"5"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Data=
bricks MCP installed</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"6"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Gong=
 MCP installed</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"7"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Sale=
sforce MCP installed</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"8"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Tool=
 permissions configured (Always Allow / Always Ask)</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"9"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Powe=
rPoint plugin installed</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"10"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Exc=
el plugin installed</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"11"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">Cla=
ude browser extension installed (Chrome or Edge)</span></li>
<li data-inline-task-id=3D"12"><span class=3D"placeholder-inline-tasks">All=
 three live tasks completed successfully</span></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"c66ef3e21dc2">
<h2 local-id=3D"82b875982dbb" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Step1=E2=80=94Installthedesktopapp">Step 1 =E2=80=94 Install the deskt=
op app</h2>
<p local-id=3D"f9be26706361">The desktop app is significantly more powerful=
 than Claude on the web. Don't skip this =E2=80=94 the rest of the guide as=
sumes you're using it.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"d930a071a790" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-1.1Download">1.1 Download</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"afce645a950a">
<li local-id=3D"22adc711efeb">
<p local-id=3D"680087719cfc"><strong>Mac &amp; Windows</strong>: <a class=
=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://claude.ai/download" rel=3D"nofollow">htt=
ps://claude.ai/download</a></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"756ca9cb6de9">The page detects your OS automatically.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"7b2f4b12775a" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-1.2Install">1.2 Install</h3>
<p local-id=3D"804d2e30d469"><strong>On Mac:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"590a35831ad2">
<li local-id=3D"c6cd6c4938ca">
<p local-id=3D"3aea08fe8e9f">Open the downloaded <code>.dmg</code> file</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"a750644a8e64">
<p local-id=3D"4e16bdeb9e4e">Drag the Claude icon into your <strong>Applica=
tions</strong> folder</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e1ec7f717a59">
<p local-id=3D"5cd19a0d151c">Open <strong>Applications</strong> =E2=86=92 d=
ouble-click <strong>Claude</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0ef481d786ed">
<p local-id=3D"b747da3be243">If you get a "downloaded from the internet" wa=
rning, click <strong>Open</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"44b1a5552f86"><strong>On Windows:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"66d8e61783ba">
<li local-id=3D"304d8feaeab5">
<p local-id=3D"fc3eb0c80c05">Open the downloaded <code>.exe</code> file</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"beb7e379f5e1">
<p local-id=3D"3b6cfab315ed">Click through the installer (defaults are fine=
)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"678592a127cf">
<p local-id=3D"ff1c997138b1">Claude will launch automatically when it's don=
e</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"11ae45865c9e" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-1.3Signin">1.3 Sign in</h3>
<p local-id=3D"147e2734a93b">We use Microsoft SSO at Mews.</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"2f676b1093a2">
<li local-id=3D"bf0041f6aec3">
<p local-id=3D"b7580da70f62">Click <strong>Continue with email</strong></p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"3e87e8ea9822">
<p local-id=3D"13d2c8f955b2">Enter your <strong>@mews.com</strong> email ad=
dress</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fb58d183eb9f">
<p local-id=3D"ad8263fc6634">You'll be redirected to the Mews Microsoft SSO=
 sign-in page</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"488989b6496b">
<p local-id=3D"f85eda8c4eb6">Sign in as you would for any other Mews tool</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3b0c67dcbe26">
<p local-id=3D"59db03c46d29">Approve any permissions Claude asks for</p></l=
i>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"0f11bb40fe58" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-1.4Verify">1.4 Verify</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ab2c0c534504">You should now see a window with three tabs al=
ong the top: <strong>Chat</strong>, <strong>Co-work</strong>, and <strong>C=
ode</strong>. If you see those, you're good.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"6a1c9a9acdaa">
<h2 local-id=3D"dd1c8aae9be9" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Step2=E2=80=94Understandthethreetabs(1minuteread)">Step 2 =E2=80=94 Un=
derstand the three tabs (1 minute read)</h2>
<p local-id=3D"de1308988ef3">You don't need to do anything in this step =E2=
=80=94 just know what they are.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"b3=
860e6fb7df" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b85eea9462f4">
<th data-local-id=3D"b4801934af9f" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a9ef0e6f6059">Tab</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"6ebbe132fffb" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"26c7e4c773a4">What it's for</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"84bc462a1136">
<td data-local-id=3D"838218a28cdc" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"80d02822a42a"><strong>Chat</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7338bdda7e9f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9aefde3395bd">Your daily driver. Most things you'll do, you'=
ll do here.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"44f6d8413e50">
<td data-local-id=3D"f69931c8b32f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7b258495710a"><strong>Co-work</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ea56d88782d5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c800785163fe">Chat with horsepower. Creates proper documents=
 (Word, Excel, PowerPoint) and can work across a folder of files on your de=
sktop.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"a955ce8034f8">
<td data-local-id=3D"0404b3fd12ed" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d2287d5d0be1"><strong>Code</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2f9e177f3a08" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7b98e3008986">For development work. Ignore unless you're wri=
ting code.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<blockquote local-id=3D"e0105206c22f">
<p local-id=3D"0e96f3c466ea"><strong>Don't agonise.</strong> Chat and Co-wo=
rk are converging. Pick whichever feels right and move on.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"8d727d8bb487">
<h2 local-id=3D"9913b8e9c2aa" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Step3=E2=80=94Installthebuilt-inplugins">Step 3 =E2=80=94 Install the =
built-in plugins</h2>
<p local-id=3D"db60b5ded0bf">These are pre-built and live inside the deskto=
p app. They take ~30 seconds each.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"2a31ac59a2c4" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-3.1Opentheconnectorsscreen">3.1 Open the connectors screen</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"2f76867c9a8d">
<li local-id=3D"9a4770d5add8">
<p local-id=3D"9b4da894c5e8">Click your <strong>profile icon</strong> (top-=
right of the desktop app)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"db915ce75d63">
<p local-id=3D"c81e8967bdc6">Click <strong>Settings</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1a31787e454e">
<p local-id=3D"6848a93bde01">In the left sidebar, click <strong>Connectors<=
/strong></p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"bc335b4c427a">You'll see a list of available connectors. The=
 next three each follow the same pattern: click <strong>Connect</strong> =
=E2=86=92 sign in =E2=86=92 approve scopes =E2=86=92 done.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"9d29378f6490" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-3.2InstallSlack">3.2 Install Slack</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"2abbace7010e">
<li local-id=3D"33ee15272b8a">
<p local-id=3D"359017161c33">Find <strong>Slack</strong> in the list</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"b5fbb733db16">
<p local-id=3D"b1e75f738b3b">Click <strong>Connect</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4b2d45f20d41">
<p local-id=3D"703c626a9d4c">A popup opens =E2=80=94 click <strong>Allow</s=
trong> to open your browser</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"147da9a9c2a0">
<p local-id=3D"4bad11ddcd76">In Slack's auth screen, choose the <strong>Mew=
s</strong> workspace</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ddf9e07c0994">
<p local-id=3D"220c236ab27f">Click <strong>Allow</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"27f1c3fa5f03">
<p local-id=3D"387e05b75997">The browser will say "you can close this tab" =
=E2=80=94 close it and return to Claude</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c35f1dacd7b2">
<p local-id=3D"7f340fd5db3e">Slack should now show as <strong>Connected</st=
rong> with a green dot</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"dff6f8945d71" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-3.3InstallAtlassian(Confluence+Jira)">3.3 Install Atlassian (Confluenc=
e + Jira)</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"a879aeea8bdf">
<li local-id=3D"30712e2c616f">
<p local-id=3D"4d5981ef15b0">Back in <strong>Settings =E2=86=92 Connectors<=
/strong>, find <strong>Atlassian</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"16b81edd64a3">
<p local-id=3D"0e0cdf874bd2">Click <strong>Connect</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bdd09e5b5b70">
<p local-id=3D"dce97051c122">Sign in via Microsoft SSO with your <strong>@m=
ews.com</strong> account</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e2e46f384846">
<p local-id=3D"781fc26510b1">Choose the <strong>Mews</strong> site when ask=
ed</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"94b45df7dfb8">
<p local-id=3D"3d64519f9b42">Click <strong>Accept</strong> on the scopes sc=
reen</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1788a9a03661">
<p local-id=3D"dbe729b577e1">Confirm it shows as <strong>Connected</strong>=
</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"599afb163ec3" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-3.4InstallMicrosoft365">3.4 Install Microsoft 365</h3>
<p local-id=3D"adf8d2a896ee">This one covers Outlook, Teams, SharePoint, an=
d OneDrive in one go.</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"82820fd4f91f">
<li local-id=3D"6db3b2ffd205">
<p local-id=3D"e7976dd1db55">Find <strong>Microsoft 365</strong> in the lis=
t</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c2ee8711cb3f">
<p local-id=3D"df359c5dbd32">Click <strong>Connect</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"04667fba01ee">
<p local-id=3D"ba7acb90504a">Sign in via Microsoft SSO</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"beabb6e357c9">
<p local-id=3D"590becbce79b">Approve the scopes</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5c7e1e7268d4">
<p local-id=3D"053af56be588">Confirm it shows as <strong>Connected</strong>=
</p></li>
</ol>
<blockquote local-id=3D"2600a5ff483f">
<p local-id=3D"559f6c342848"><strong>If a connector won't authenticate</str=
ong>, sign out of Claude completely (profile icon =E2=86=92 Sign out), reop=
en the app, sign back in, and retry. Fixes ~80% of OAuth weirdness.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"67e42d207d7d">
<h2 local-id=3D"3813d0dfe182" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Step4=E2=80=94InstallthelocalMCPs">Step 4 =E2=80=94 Install the local =
MCPs</h2>
<p local-id=3D"839ac25626cf">MCPs (Model Context Protocol servers) are exte=
nsions that give Claude access to tools that don't have a built-in connecto=
r. Mews has packaged ours as <code>.mcpb</code> files (Model Context Protoc=
ol Bundles) =E2=80=94 single files you double-click to install.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"d36bd7af76af" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-How.mcpbfileswork=E2=80=94readthisonce">How <code>.mcpb</code> files w=
ork =E2=80=94 read this once</h3>
<p local-id=3D"c9087f9dcc2d"><strong>Method 1 (preferred, Mac only):</stron=
g> Download the <code>.mcpb</code> =E2=86=92 double-click =E2=86=92 Claude =
opens an install dialog =E2=86=92 click <strong>Install</strong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"d49d11428a6f"><strong>Method 2 (Windows, or if Method 1 gets=
 stuck on Mac):</strong> Open Claude =E2=86=92 <strong>Settings =E2=86=92 E=
xtensions =E2=86=92 Advanced =E2=86=92 Install Extension</strong> =E2=86=92=
 select the <code>.mcpb</code> file from your downloads.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5c0ec974c7f6">After installing either way:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"50c1afda7a50">
<li local-id=3D"70414deaad33">
<p local-id=3D"78207554b05e">The MCP shows up under <strong>Settings =E2=86=
=92 Extensions</strong> as <strong>Installed</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cd7b81107e77">
<p local-id=3D"86f44b4a7edf"><strong>Restart the desktop app</strong> =E2=
=80=94 MCPs only register on launch</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0ed9c47041b3">
<p local-id=3D"cfd4dee33e83">Some MCPs need additional config (tokens, env =
vars) =E2=80=94 see the per-MCP steps below</p></li>
</ol>
<blockquote local-id=3D"22ea9984f9c8">
<p local-id=3D"8bd47e0b54fb"><strong>Heads-up:</strong> if you double-click=
 a <code>.mcpb</code> link inside Confluence, it'll try to unzip it. Right-=
click =E2=86=92 <strong>Save link as</strong> instead, or use the download =
button in Confluence's link preview.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"c6e71a6191be">
<h3 local-id=3D"5843ee93c330" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-4.1Databricks">4.1 Databricks</h3>
<p local-id=3D"d08f6097cad7"><strong>4.1.1 Download and install the MCPB</s=
trong></p>
<p class=3D"media-group"><img height=3D"250" style=3D"margin: 2px; border: =
1px solid #ddd; box-sizing: border-box; vertical-align: text-bottom;" src=
=3D"c7aefe167a2b518ab1efb79d2c97dcf0ecd989d729795e6d2236dc225789147b" width=
=3D"250"></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"ab8b8dc23adc">
<li local-id=3D"aa1b882177d6">
<p local-id=3D"39c03937357e">Download: <strong>Databricks MCPB above.</stro=
ng></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f30fbc65d62c">
<p local-id=3D"e8a46b3bd271">Install via Method 1 or Method 2 above</p></li=
>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"f866c1b549c7"><strong>4.1.2 Get your Databricks personal acc=
ess token</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"3f802a5b98e7">
<li local-id=3D"4c3c0f89ca3a">
<p local-id=3D"64dafea9048e">Open the dev Databricks workspace: <a class=3D=
"external-link" href=3D"https://adb-5769108933149883.3.azuredatabricks.net/=
" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>https://adb-5769108933149883.3.azuredatabricks.n=
et/</strong></a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4715d17d56d2">
<p local-id=3D"14610b3b8f4b">Sign in with your Mews account via SSO. If you=
 can't log in at all, ping Data Platform =E2=80=94 they'll need to adjust y=
our access (they handle this in tickets like DATA-6010)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e25f22f94218">
<p local-id=3D"8132dee44622">Top-right menu =E2=86=92 <strong>Settings =E2=
=86=92 Developer =E2=86=92 Access tokens</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"da4c0bfc0d9c">
<p local-id=3D"85e0110be69e">Click <strong>Generate new token</strong></p><=
/li>
<li local-id=3D"4d82928b7527">
<p local-id=3D"82eee9ee9a4f">Optionally set a description and expiry</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"b89dc0eee0c4">
<p local-id=3D"b0230de09510">Click <strong>Create</strong> and <strong>copy=
 the token somewhere secure immediately</strong> =E2=80=94 you won't see it=
 again</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"6c2427e7b12a"><strong>4.1.3 Configure the MCP</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"ca196af8f5a4">When the MCP asks for environment variables, p=
aste these in:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">DATABRI=
CKS_HOST=3Dhttps://adb-5769108933149883.3.azuredatabricks.net
DATABRICKS_SQL_WAREHOUSE_ID=3D3fad3bbb3022870c
DATABRICKS_TOKEN=3D&lt;the token you just generated&gt;</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"0d1c8f669312"><strong>4.1.4 Restart Claude.</strong></p>
<hr local-id=3D"51893d3c2b6d">
<h3 local-id=3D"0d6fd90d8d7b" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-4.2Gong">4.2 Gong</h3>
<p local-id=3D"e95aab217329"><strong>4.2.1 Download and install the MCPB</s=
trong></p>
<p class=3D"media-group"><img height=3D"250" style=3D"margin: 2px; border: =
1px solid #ddd; box-sizing: border-box; vertical-align: text-bottom;" src=
=3D"9237533f8d4973718a72bde5ff867d696935694359e4442122c07f754164281f" width=
=3D"250"></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"90deb96b3068">
<li local-id=3D"20182a9934b5">
<p local-id=3D"b4cf9ee89c9a">Download: <strong>Gong MCPB above</strong></p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"57726f31bed9">
<p local-id=3D"164b4c81bd63">Install via Method 1 or Method 2 above</p></li=
>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"aeaf6962289c"><strong>4.2.2 Configure</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"021dee63b033">When prompted, paste your <strong>Gong API key=
</strong>. If you don't have one, your manager or RevOps can issue one =E2=
=80=94 message in <code>#ran-ai</code> if you're stuck.</p>
<p local-id=3D"81917e8646e3"><strong>4.2.3 Restart Claude.</strong></p>
<hr local-id=3D"0a2498f1d9fa">
<h3 local-id=3D"5ca0ae0ad73d" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-4.3Salesforce">4.3 Salesforce</h3>
<p local-id=3D"54f065f37376"><strong>4.3.1 Download and install the MCPB</s=
trong></p>
<p class=3D"media-group"><img height=3D"250" style=3D"margin: 2px; border: =
1px solid #ddd; box-sizing: border-box; vertical-align: text-bottom;" src=
=3D"e2069f099cd43085bae9167373c7eff4a9e02177238464769168bddf9a93cafc" width=
=3D"250"></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"ef97a01c5116">
<li local-id=3D"753b5dac9b2a">
<p local-id=3D"2526ab02fbcd">Download: <strong>Salesforce MCPB above</stron=
g></p>
<ul local-id=3D"b58e8d6c5762">
<li local-id=3D"7d09ba8b9b4b">
<p local-id=3D"9023d216314e"><strong>Heads-up</strong>: if the link is in C=
onfluence, <strong>don't double-click it</strong> =E2=80=94 that'll unzip i=
t inside the page. Right-click =E2=86=92 <strong>Download</strong> instead.=
</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"5b9501f08620">
<p local-id=3D"62b71baede43">Install via Method 1 (Mac) or Method 2 (Window=
s or stuck Mac)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1e58a2582a44">
<p local-id=3D"8f6562586237"><strong>Fully quit and relaunch Claude</strong=
> =E2=80=94 quit from the Mac menu bar / Windows system tray, not just clos=
e the window</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"5b0309b71101"><strong>4.3.2 Run the activation prompt</stron=
g></p>
<p local-id=3D"ad35468c1a53">This step links your Mews Salesforce identity =
to the connector and teaches Claude about our specific Salesforce setup.</p=
>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"2d2be5309e1e">
<li local-id=3D"d985170e96ed">
<p local-id=3D"72cdcd79f0c6">Open a <strong>brand-new chat</strong> in Clau=
de</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9ec056441d07">
<p local-id=3D"924a04dc18f3">A browser window will open for a one-time Prod=
uction login =E2=80=94 sign in</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8c11f6cb5c1b">
<p local-id=3D"af06b2982949">The connector will then map every custom objec=
t, field, and picklist available to your profile (this takes a minute or tw=
o)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cd1b5dcf344b">
<p local-id=3D"7844f2b1f61d">When it says "Installation Complete", you're d=
one</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"062a2c43468f"><strong>4.3.3 Pro-tip =E2=80=94 save credits d=
uring setup</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"270c70301bb2">Before running the activation prompt:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"2a587a470bcb">
<li local-id=3D"b2ab265bb839">
<p local-id=3D"fc6f6c8e52b7">Switch your model to <strong>Claude Haiku</str=
ong> (cheapest/fastest) just for the setup phase. Once it says "Installatio=
n Complete", switch back to Sonnet/Opus for real work.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5a822e0fe62c">
<p local-id=3D"b53895a4ca5f">We'll set the Salesforce tools to <strong>Alwa=
ys Allow</strong> in <strong>Step 5</strong> =E2=80=94 that prevents Claude=
 pausing to ask for permission on every call and saves credits during the "=
Learn" phase.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"c715ce049a56"><strong>4.3.4 Troubleshooting</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"701e24ec975e">
<li local-id=3D"6c50199cad3d">
<p local-id=3D"1f9106e6cd2a">"Security Mismatch / Invalid State" =E2=86=92 =
restart Claude, run the activation prompt again in a fresh chat</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"622a03105fa8">
<p local-id=3D"dd3c9dd47352">Auth fails repeatedly =E2=86=92 fully quit Cla=
ude (menu bar / system tray), relaunch, retry</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"71443a80afba">
<h3 local-id=3D"8202523ed040" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-4.4Verifyallthreeareworking">4.4 Verify all three are working</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"f482fbfe3d87">
<li local-id=3D"d660fd3e80d0">
<p local-id=3D"90f6f32d2613">Open a new Chat</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8ea1b69f7d1a">
<p local-id=3D"aa38e26869d3">Type: <strong>"What MCP tools do you have acce=
ss to?"</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fad699e4208b">
<p local-id=3D"ce4c15c93b09">You should see Databricks, Gong, and Salesforc=
e listed</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"a5599b5fd98f">If any are missing, go to <strong>Settings =E2=
=86=92 Extensions</strong>, find the one with a red status, and click it fo=
r the error message =E2=80=94 it'll usually tell you exactly what's missing=
.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"0a0c5f270b6c">
<h2 local-id=3D"a74477b26106" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Step5=E2=80=94Setyourtoolpermissions">Step 5 =E2=80=94 Set your tool p=
ermissions</h2>
<p local-id=3D"8b51b853a8db">Now that Claude has access to a bunch of tools=
, you get to decide how trusting you want to be about each one. This is wor=
th 5 minutes of setup =E2=80=94 it makes everything faster afterwards.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"7d858bdb1c2f" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Howpermissionswork">How permissions work</h3>
<p local-id=3D"f3212c0b388e">Every connector and MCP exposes individual <st=
rong>tools</strong> to Claude (e.g. the Slack connector has <code>send_mess=
age</code>, <code>read_channel</code>, <code>search_messages</code>, etc.).=
 For each tool, you can set one of three modes:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"e8=
3243daefba" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"a3187122d573">
<th data-local-id=3D"a7063a6bc66f" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"6a31dfc07dcb">Mode</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"0b6939d5900b" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"8035bb50e1b8">What happens</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"69a0566b015f">
<td data-local-id=3D"12082c174b89" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"010dae67adcd"><strong>Always Ask</strong> <em>(default)</em>=
</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"fc823126cec8" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c636bd35b768">Claude pauses and asks you to approve every ti=
me it wants to use this tool. Safe but slow.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"1df5b519b366">
<td data-local-id=3D"ee448828163b" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"03088717efb8"><strong>Always Allow</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"24c81dbbc1b4" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"db62aa3ff579">Claude uses the tool freely without asking. Fa=
st but commits you to whatever it does.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"700348e7f058">
<td data-local-id=3D"131b50765cdd" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ef2b15826691"><strong>Always Deny</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3a6c8e4bfc6f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b04bd07fad9c">Claude can never use this tool, even if you as=
k it to.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"12977ac4ff1b">You can also approve <strong>just for this ses=
sion</strong> in the moment =E2=80=94 that lets Claude use the tool freely =
until you close the chat, then it goes back to asking.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"c4afb48774f2" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Wheretosetthem">Where to set them</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"be9865a79c96">
<li local-id=3D"9da4f593dda3">
<p local-id=3D"ad34384ed4e4"><strong>Settings =E2=86=92 Extensions</strong>=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0dba5e9e192e">
<p local-id=3D"47f6c8ac9eb5">Click the extension/connector you want to conf=
igure (e.g. <strong>Slack</strong>)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"726b75c415e5">
<p local-id=3D"11e993353592">You'll see a list of every tool that extension=
 provides</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"80a19d69596a">
<p local-id=3D"5a42c2d9a59a">Toggle each one to <strong>Always Allow</stron=
g>, <strong>Always Ask</strong>, or <strong>Always Deny</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"d7e4563ebd30">You can also set them on the fly: when Claude =
asks for permission in a chat, the popup has an <strong>"Always allow this =
tool"</strong> option you can tick.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"35b76f6c297d" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Sensibledefaults">Sensible defaults</h3>
<p local-id=3D"6ad099e76905">Two simple rules of thumb:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"93fdf17797cc">
<li local-id=3D"c06e75bfe59c">
<p local-id=3D"a8258eeb5d5c"><strong>Read-only tools =E2=86=92 Always Allow=
.</strong> Reading a Slack channel, querying Salesforce, looking at your ca=
lendar, browsing files. Claude can't break anything by reading. Asking for =
permission every time is just friction.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b9499f19bbaf">
<p local-id=3D"c41e79e6e39c"><strong>Write/destructive tools =E2=86=92 Alwa=
ys Ask.</strong> Sending Slack messages, updating Salesforce records, sendi=
ng emails, deleting files. You want a moment to look at what Claude's about=
 to do before it does it.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e02302c0c690">A starter config that works for most people:</=
p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"2c=
002c3bb33f" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"384bae1b659a">
<th data-local-id=3D"18875e4a5a4b" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"c7545aa6a41c">Tool category</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"b59e03b901e5" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"1154e40fb19a">Recommended mode</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"5701a2e4439c">
<td data-local-id=3D"6f430c321ce2" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a7762eefd328">Slack =E2=80=94 read channel, search, read DMs=
</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"fdab041ec710" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ae4b3e1756cd">Always Allow</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"db1ec9cfa63d">
<td data-local-id=3D"fdef27916a2d" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a0765af968d3">Slack =E2=80=94 send message, send DM</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e3194b468677" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9cdecc679702">Always Ask</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"7f899b824109">
<td data-local-id=3D"395ab29a28b2" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"deb5a5e02e6c">Salesforce =E2=80=94 query, describe, learn</p=
></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4b7f37165793" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"71c9b6fec425">Always Allow</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"bd1d6227a0c6">
<td data-local-id=3D"ef44f6e439a8" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e657f5c6b01c">Salesforce =E2=80=94 create, update, delete</p=
></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d4218cd9bda6" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4893e7751737">Always Ask</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"9887e1618413">
<td data-local-id=3D"9292070041c5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f26e4e626d75">Outlook / M365 =E2=80=94 read calendar, search=
 email</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"394f58968167" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d8958e89fd79">Always Allow</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"e4276f75ebbb">
<td data-local-id=3D"6773e8a58873" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d8bdd0e3b001">Outlook / M365 =E2=80=94 send email, create ev=
ent</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7d5374fd4e22" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"305e62e2a876">Always Ask</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c27192456e86">
<td data-local-id=3D"223722bd88dc" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3ba543decc85">Confluence / Jira =E2=80=94 read, search</p></=
td>
<td data-local-id=3D"90ca7e5f4e5b" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"765a58bf607a">Always Allow</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ce51f5537ad1">
<td data-local-id=3D"8411fda96a4e" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0940e1bc158e">Confluence / Jira =E2=80=94 create, update</p>=
</td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0f3e5bc6859d" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f29345735eec">Always Ask</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"34e507ea7adc">
<td data-local-id=3D"4ed457fb6773" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a240b1c70923">Databricks =E2=80=94 query (read-only by defau=
lt)</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2df903b24047" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"588d4cf88ded">Always Allow</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"14ccc225078a">
<td data-local-id=3D"1adc5210a5da" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bf9cd547d2d8">Gong =E2=80=94 read calls, search</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"9a621449573c" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4b58c31566de">Always Allow</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"fc9e7537c9e9">
<td data-local-id=3D"2de488975ba9" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ed44f897bfe3">File system (Co-work) =E2=80=94 read</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"50ddbc452358" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2634e3b6dc99">Always Allow</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"7ccba49029ba">
<td data-local-id=3D"3619642c219a" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"18427b524444">File system (Co-work) =E2=80=94 write, delete,=
 move</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"dd1d496f39e4" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0d01aef57670">Always Ask</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"26a7e9e32dd3" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Whythisalsosavesyoumoney">Why this also saves you money</h3>
<p local-id=3D"332c1c51b68b">Every time Claude has to stop and ask for perm=
ission, it re-reads the conversation context to figure out what to do next.=
 That costs tokens. Setting read-only tools to Always Allow keeps Claude's =
"thought process" lean and your spend down.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"c93d178c1b96" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Youcanchangeyourmindanytime">You can change your mind any time</h3>
<p local-id=3D"386938d71259">Permissions aren't binding. If you set somethi=
ng to Always Allow and regret it later, go back to <strong>Settings =E2=86=
=92 Extensions =E2=86=92 [tool]</strong> and flip it. Same for the other di=
rection.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"3687a161c768">
<h2 local-id=3D"cfaece5445e7" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Step6=E2=80=94Installthedocumentplugins">Step 6 =E2=80=94 Install the =
document plugins</h2>
<p local-id=3D"24ff10a9763b">These let Claude (especially in Co-work) creat=
e real <code>.pptx</code> and <code>.xlsx</code> files instead of describin=
g what they'd contain.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"4db6ce7d6018" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-6.1OpentheClaudepluginstore">6.1 Open the Claude plugin store</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"d42a78cb6c3b">
<li local-id=3D"ee23aec23d4e">
<p local-id=3D"70406a4a5d54">In the desktop app: <strong>Settings =E2=86=92=
 Extensions</strong> (or click the <strong>Extensions</strong> icon in the =
sidebar)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1952b85701c9">
<p local-id=3D"fae7e666681a">Click <strong>Browse extensions</strong> / <st=
rong>Browse store</strong></p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"f43bc399f5fb">Or open the store directly: <a class=3D"extern=
al-link" href=3D"https://claude.ai/extensions" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>htt=
ps://claude.ai/extensions</strong></a></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"0f579c69e32e" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-6.2PowerPointplugin">6.2 PowerPoint plugin</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"9bd0bc3e6339">
<li local-id=3D"bbef81d41667">
<p local-id=3D"dd18f84e7e95">In the store, search for <strong>PowerPoint</s=
trong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fc99b0458f9c">
<p local-id=3D"f95ac1596ab8">Find the official <strong>Anthropic PowerPoint=
</strong> Add-In</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d2af3c5aaec1">
<p local-id=3D"03cf3e1dc9a9">Click <strong>Install</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"532d4727c063">
<p local-id=3D"2c70d5ec09fe">No auth required</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"59f82a2ef76b" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-6.3Excelplugin">6.3 Excel plugin</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"3dc9cfd73c3d">
<li local-id=3D"e3c33ad0bca4">
<p local-id=3D"13ecce7c60d1">In the store, search for <strong>Excel</strong=
></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d4fadf24fdc9">
<p local-id=3D"761dac22c7e8">Find the official <strong>Anthropic Excel</str=
ong> Add-In</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"aa5a5bf8b7d0">
<p local-id=3D"5b0696e31358">Click <strong>Install</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0e69ec18672b">
<p local-id=3D"d759e31cbd0a">No auth required</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"a7321106e471" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-6.4Verify">6.4 Verify</h3>
<p local-id=3D"4bece77b574a">In Co-work, type: <strong>"Make me a tiny 3-sl=
ide test deck about cats."</strong> If a <code>.pptx</code> file appears in=
 your output, you're good.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"e685fabc0d65">
<h2 local-id=3D"3884c85d8d19" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Step7=E2=80=94Installthebrowserextension">Step 7 =E2=80=94 Install the=
 browser extension</h2>
<p local-id=3D"5bd68d1ffa0c">Lets Claude take actions inside your browser t=
abs (clicking, filling forms, reading authenticated pages).</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"42d952ab1348" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-7.1InstallinChrome">7.1 Install in Chrome</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"62beb82e5047">
<li local-id=3D"1902eb18d88a">
<p local-id=3D"367d3d33c1d1">Go to: <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http=
s://chromewebstore.google.com/search/claude%20anthropic" rel=3D"nofollow"><=
strong>Claude for Chrome =E2=80=94 Web Store listing</strong></a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"83a4d8144e72">
<p local-id=3D"2356598f78a6">Find the official one =E2=80=94 publisher: <st=
rong>Anthropic</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ff48138fafea">
<p local-id=3D"86087d26590c">Click <strong>Add to Chrome</strong> =E2=86=92=
 <strong>Add extension</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cce0ecfaeec2">
<p local-id=3D"058f3ab7e62f">Pin it to your toolbar: click the puzzle-piece=
 icon in Chrome =E2=86=92 click the pin next to <strong>Claude</strong></p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"2ca9d7662121">
<p local-id=3D"b361ea400975">Click the Claude extension icon and sign in wi=
th your Claude account</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"ab013af72815" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-7.2InstallinEdge">7.2 Install in Edge</h3>
<p local-id=3D"03f5342a0742">The same Chrome Web Store extension works in E=
dge. Either:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"51b8417969ff">
<li local-id=3D"f0cf642e7480">
<p local-id=3D"a60120eb964f">Open the Web Store link above in Edge =E2=80=
=94 Edge will offer to install it</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"14a236d658e7">
<p local-id=3D"46208cdcee73">Or enable "Allow extensions from other stores"=
 in Edge settings first if it doesn't appear</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"f42a5b006c80" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-7.3RestartClaude">7.3 Restart Claude</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ddbcd9181ae5">Restart the Claude desktop app so it sees the =
extension.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"8dc69d0d1c48" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-7.4Verify">7.4 Verify</h3>
<p local-id=3D"833230f7fd2b">In Chat, ask: <strong>"List my connected brows=
ers."</strong> You should see Chrome (or Edge) in the list.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"59062f3780f1">
<h2 local-id=3D"029b4658b7ea" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Step8=E2=80=94Findyourusage">Step 8 =E2=80=94 Find your usage</h2>
<p local-id=3D"454da41219ca">Always know what you've got left.</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"2d62d42eea4e">
<li local-id=3D"d1c2b3525225">
<p local-id=3D"87e8e980faa9">Profile icon (top-right) =E2=86=92 <strong>Set=
tings</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7a5c8c7d6a22">
<p local-id=3D"dc2110f13125">Sidebar =E2=86=92 <strong>Usage</strong></p></=
li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"d5c223638fdf">You'll see:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"45ed90399a7a">
<li local-id=3D"d970374202f1">
<p local-id=3D"3e9b92ef7d56">Spend used this month</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8f33214bcaae">
<p local-id=3D"4e3758074338">Spend remaining</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"33e660925d73">
<p local-id=3D"08f6546a5cfb">Reset date</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"bd00d7eb0bd5">Glance at this weekly for the first month unti=
l you have a feel for it.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"1d99fc7c659d">
<h2 local-id=3D"2b738e1e5ad5" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Step9=E2=80=94Tryit(threelivetasks)">Step 9 =E2=80=94 Try it (three li=
ve tasks)</h2>
<p local-id=3D"554ea85e4402">Don't skip these. The fastest way to know it's=
 all working =E2=80=94 and start to feel what Claude can do =E2=80=94 is to=
 make it do something.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"fb67e9d83476" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Task1=E2=80=94MakeClaudesoundlikeyou">Task 1 =E2=80=94 Make Claude sou=
nd like you</h3>
<p local-id=3D"a7f8ce6b398a">In Chat, paste:</p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"19ed66d2d336">
<p local-id=3D"42a2a7eda1b5">Read the last month of Slack messages I've sen=
t =E2=80=94 across DMs, threads, and channels. Then create a skill called "=
How I write on Slack" that captures my tone, sentence length, signature wor=
ds, where I use emoji, where I'm direct vs. softening, and how I open and c=
lose messages. Save it as a skill so I can re-use it.</p>
</blockquote>
<p local-id=3D"3af94a11f11e">What this teaches you:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7b40b22663bc">
<li local-id=3D"c8772d20b679">
<p local-id=3D"a85fcf59d764">How Claude pulls from Slack</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c945465bae82">
<p local-id=3D"ec9b5c5490fb">What a skill is and how creating one feels</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"1ca5c31f5204">
<p local-id=3D"5f4207dc1df5">Why it's worth investing 5 minutes to teach Cl=
aude things you'll need a hundred times</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"8f02254d75bc" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Task2=E2=80=94OrganiseyourDownloadsfolder">Task 2 =E2=80=94 Organise y=
our Downloads folder</h3>
<p local-id=3D"b9428306492b">Switch to <strong>Co-work</strong>. Drag your =
<strong>Downloads</strong> folder into the chat (or click the file/folder p=
icker =E2=86=92 choose Downloads).</p>
<p local-id=3D"05d5de55a7d9">Then ask:</p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"f91dbc06e096">
<p local-id=3D"baabb39f74d6">Have a look at the contents of this folder. Su=
ggest a sensible structure based on what's actually in there =E2=80=94 by f=
ile type, by topic, by date, whatever makes sense. Then create the new fold=
ers and move the files into them. Ask me before deleting anything.</p>
</blockquote>
<p local-id=3D"1740facb9c1d">What this teaches you:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6e955ac5e7c7">
<li local-id=3D"e7c0a73c83f5">
<p local-id=3D"b121026b8d08">Co-work's ability to work across a real folder=
 on your machine</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"34ea311cdbc4">
<p local-id=3D"dd288f7fd32f">That Claude can take real actions on your file=
system, not just describe them</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1916a491fdbf">
<p local-id=3D"6f252a1ce475">How permission prompts work when an agent is a=
bout to do something destructive</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"2315c30fb2d0" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Task3=E2=80=94Prepyourselfforyournextexternalmeeting">Task 3 =E2=80=94=
 Prep yourself for your next external meeting</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ed9fc0c3c3e3">In Chat or Co-work:</p>
<blockquote local-id=3D"781f992a396a">
<p local-id=3D"3d999c0a7723">Find my next external meeting in Outlook. Look=
 up the company in Salesforce. Pull our most recent Gong calls with anyone =
from that company. Then create a one-page Word doc prep brief for me =E2=80=
=94 include who I'm meeting, what we last talked about, where the deal/acco=
unt stands, and three things I should ask or raise.</p>
</blockquote>
<p local-id=3D"1d50fffeed5d">What this teaches you:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a884c39c45fc">
<li local-id=3D"5bfd9927776a">
<p local-id=3D"e9e7a466d3d7">That Claude can chain across multiple connecto=
rs (Outlook + Salesforce + Gong)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4a6d7f3f9256">
<p local-id=3D"e9d831435b95">That the output is a real artefact (a Word doc=
) you can edit and share</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"475b19a2a027">
<p local-id=3D"13f6148dce26">The shape of a workflow you'll probably end up=
 running every Monday morning</p></li>
</ul>
<blockquote local-id=3D"50139502997b">
<p local-id=3D"c09c34da25fa"><strong>If any task fails:</strong> the error =
will name the connector that's missing or broken. Go back to Step 3 or 4 an=
d re-check that connector.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"87d87f154659">
<h2 local-id=3D"b69ae2db8523" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Step10=E2=80=94Goingfurther">Step 10 =E2=80=94 Going further</h2>
<p local-id=3D"3f488a60c168">A few things worth knowing now that you're set=
 up.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"c8488a0647d0" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Getbetteratprompting">Get better at prompting</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"e73a1af24ec8">
<li local-id=3D"8e58b74302d8">
<p local-id=3D"f7d3aa46a0c2"><strong>Be specific.</strong> "Write a Slack m=
essage" is weak. "Write a 3-line Slack message to my team thanking them for=
 hitting Q2 targets, in my voice" is strong.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"857bf7bf0f1d">
<p local-id=3D"a3f7401c45a2"><strong>Give it context.</strong> Drag in the =
doc, paste the Salesforce link, share the Gong call. The more relevant cont=
ext, the better the output.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2071632ac8a0">
<p local-id=3D"44bb0f0683a4"><strong>Iterate.</strong> The first answer is =
rarely the final one. Tell it what's off and ask again =E2=80=94 it's not o=
ffended.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f5065212242a">
<p local-id=3D"fac265e40c1b"><strong>Use examples.</strong> "Like this emai=
l I sent last week" works better than describing the tone abstractly.</p></=
li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"8fc34f8ff80e" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Howtokensgetused">How tokens get used</h3>
<p local-id=3D"19961c9c4a65">Every word in and out costs tokens. The bigges=
t spenders:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"8045a10036c5">
<li local-id=3D"a6f3dbf86618">
<p local-id=3D"28c2945e5d68">Long pasted documents (paste once, then refer =
back rather than re-pasting)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"781faac5db43">
<p local-id=3D"2df5c0bf942f">Long-running threads (start a fresh chat for u=
nrelated topics)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9e6ea7b22027">
<p local-id=3D"f47a10bdf236">Very large folders in Co-work</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c7277325ae50">Don't worry too much =E2=80=94 just don't past=
e a 200-page PDF every time you ask a question.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"a24c836bc94d" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Whatit'sgoodatrightnow">What it's good at right now</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"5c0c15b78d29">
<li local-id=3D"a4f66c40a585">
<p local-id=3D"aa5f7c0b2047">Drafting Slack messages, emails, follow-ups</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"47d2fc6cd7b1">
<p local-id=3D"f603e1f0c26f">Meeting prep across Outlook + Salesforce + Gon=
g</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"425d2fcc5d6d">
<p local-id=3D"92f12a0bfc10">Summarising long threads, calls, and docs</p><=
/li>
<li local-id=3D"b5048dcd21f5">
<p local-id=3D"b478438923b5">Building decks, Word docs, Excel sheets from e=
xisting material</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"14d27a73137b">
<p local-id=3D"ab23437647af">Pulling numbers from Databricks</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"64d0a9ae710a">
<p local-id=3D"d928b0b6ed3f">Writing skills you can reuse forever</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"18b18ac9d162" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Buildyourownskills">Build your own skills</h3>
<p local-id=3D"0febcc515fb0">When you find yourself doing the same thing tw=
ice =E2=80=94 a weekly update, a 1:1 prep, a status report =E2=80=94 turn i=
t into a skill. It takes 5 minutes the first time and saves 5 minutes every=
 time after that.</p>
<p local-id=3D"bafcf8437ac3">Charlie's library of ready-made skills you can=
 copy: <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://mewssystems-my.sharepoint=
.com/:f:/g/personal/charlie_delamare_mews_com/IgA1QzKGAx_gTakh0aR6Y6mrAQKox=
vkPyLXj0vL4bgUHXPc?e=3DLfL0lA" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>SharePoint folder</=
strong></a></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"9fe0ff0b19f5" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Keepupwiththeteam">Keep up with the team</h3>
<p local-id=3D"4d0f195ddd78">The <strong>#ran-ai</strong> channel in Slack =
is where the team is sharing what's working, what's broken, and what's wort=
h trying. Lurk first, ask when you've got something.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"859e76efd4c0">
<h2 local-id=3D"19d0cbbc72e0" id=3D"GettingStartedwithClaude=E2=80=94SetupG=
uide-Stuck?">Stuck?</h2>
<p local-id=3D"e750449be18b">Two options, in this order:</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"5e038f823a07">
<li local-id=3D"b50a0c7359ab">
<p local-id=3D"ea8bad2a571f"><strong>Ask Claude.</strong> Seriously =E2=80=
=94 paste the error, describe what you're trying to do, and ask it to help.=
 It's surprisingly good at debugging itself.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"27d117ab28ec">
<p local-id=3D"f463f9403917"><strong>Ping me on Slack</strong> =E2=80=94 <s=
trong>@Charlie Delamare</strong>. Or post in <strong>#ran-ai</strong> so th=
e team can see the answer too.</p></li>
</ol>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
